chunks.html_content: You must tell DVLA if you have pulmonary arterial hypertension and you’re receiving treatment from an NHS specialist centre.
chunks.plain_content:
Pulmonary arterial hypertension and driving
You must tell DVLA if you have pulmonary arterial hypertension and you’re receiving treatment from an NHS specialist centre.

chunks.html_content: You can be fined up to £1,000 if you do not tell DVLA about a condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.
chunks.plain_content:
Pulmonary arterial hypertension and driving
You can be fined up to £1,000 if you do not tell DVLA about a condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.

chunks.html_content: Fill in form PAH1 and send it to DVLA. The address is on the form.
